Khartoum â€” Vice - President of the Republic, Hassabo Mohamed Abdul-Rahman, Wednesday chaired a meeting of the higher committee for unlicensed weapons and vehicles. In a press statement, the Minister of Information, Dr. Ahmed Bilal, said that the committee has affirmed the importance of pressing ahead in implementing the weapon's collection plan and immediate compensation to the citizens who handed over their four-wheel drive vehicles. He indicated that the higher committee has got informed on the great benefits resulting from the collection of unlicensed arms in the fields of security and stability and drop of criminal incidents and robbery cases and enhancing the social co-existence. He said that efforts in the coming stage will be directed to supporting security and combating smuggling, human trafficking and dugs.